# NBE Portal — maintenance form UI + AI rewrite rules

## Door cards: serial-only labels (manager request)

- Door header and door dropdown must prefer **serial-only** identifiers:
  - Current-style: `P0####` (e.g. `P0823`)
  - Older-style: `PJ####` (e.g. `PJ7505`)
- Do not repeat door type/extra descriptors in the door dropdown label.

## Door details + history sections

- Door details blocks should be optional and avoid duplication with notes.
- Previous history should only render when meaningful history exists (do not show an empty section by default).

## Checklist data + UX

- Checklist label text should come from a maintained list (e.g. Excel “Question” column) and remain stable.
- Floating notes should use a real tooltip (hover + click, click-away/Escape to dismiss).

## Photos: bulk upload correctness

- Bulk uploads must not lose photos due to stale-prop races.
  - When uploading concurrently, append against the latest photos array (use an internal ref) instead of `onChange([...photos, uploaded])`.
- Keep offline behavior safe (sequential is acceptable) while online can use limited concurrency.

## Downloads: user feedback while downloading

- Download actions should show a loading state and (when available) progress percent using `Content-Length`.
- Prefer a shared helper (stream response + `onProgress`) so buttons can disable during download and prevent repeated clicks.

## Signature UX (industry-standard)

- Signature canvas must be DPR-correct (CSS size vs backing store) so drawn lines align with pointer.
- Provide alternate capture modes:
  - Draw
  - Upload image (JPG/PNG/WebP)
  - Type (use existing Roboto font stack, only a few style options)

## AI rewrite: per-door “Improve / Rephrase Notes”

- The AI endpoint should behave as an editor:
  - One defect per sentence; preserve all details; no assumptions; no meta-commentary.
  - Safety-risk sentence only if explicitly stated in input.
- Repeated clicks should refine:
  - Include original notes + previous rewrite as context.
  - If output is identical to previous rewrite, retry once with a stronger “must differ” instruction.
- Keep refinement attempts convergent (lower randomness after attempt 1).

## Rate limiting and AI endpoints

- Avoid global per-IP buckets that allow unrelated API traffic to starve AI endpoints.
  - General tier identifiers should include a path key so limits are per-endpoint.

